WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:19.519 position:50% align:center
Shu, no!

00:00:19.602 --> 00:00:21.396 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:00:21.479 --> 00:00:22.856 position:50% align:center
Not Shu!

00:00:22.939 --> 00:00:26.609 position:50% align:center
People cannot surpass the
God that creates them.

00:00:26.693 --> 00:00:29.154 position:50% align:center
You're so proud of
that intellect of yours,

00:00:29.237 --> 00:00:32.073 position:50% align:center
but God's is far beyond.

00:00:32.157 --> 00:00:35.285 position:50% align:center
It's over, Shu Bi.

00:02:17.303 --> 00:02:19.556 position:50% align:center
Damn it!

00:02:19.639 --> 00:02:20.557 position:50% align:center
Arrow...

00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:23.101 position:50% align:center
Stay back! I might
erase you, too!

00:02:23.184 --> 00:02:26.771 position:50% align:center
I'm the god of death!
It's just like Rudolf said.

00:02:26.855 --> 00:02:29.607 position:50% align:center
Get away, or I'll end up
erasing all of you!

00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:31.276 position:50% align:center
I'm supposed to
destroy the world!

00:02:31.359 --> 00:02:35.447 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA laughs]
So it finally sunk in, huh?

00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:38.742 position:50% align:center
It's what you're meant to do,
better get used to it.

00:02:38.825 --> 00:02:40.952 position:50% align:center
Shut your mouth!

00:02:41.036 --> 00:02:42.328 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:02:42.412 --> 00:02:43.538 position:50% align:center
He manifested?

00:02:43.621 --> 00:02:45.832 position:50% align:center
But we just broke his
Warper, didn't we?

00:02:45.915 --> 00:02:46.958 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA]
The hard truth is,

00:02:47.042 --> 00:02:49.753 position:50% align:center
there's no escaping
from destiny.

00:02:49.836 --> 00:02:52.797 position:50% align:center
It's all going according to
the Supreme Elect's plans.

00:02:52.881 --> 00:02:55.008 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW] Would you shut
the hell up already?

00:02:55.091 --> 00:02:56.509 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA grunts]

00:02:56.593 --> 00:02:59.471 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW] If I'm really
the destroyer, then guess what?

00:02:59.554 --> 00:03:00.930 position:50% align:center
I'll destroy Rudolf!

00:03:01.014 --> 00:03:02.515 position:50% align:center
Hold on!

00:03:03.641 --> 00:03:06.186 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTÉ] Prax, have the
Lutoh citizens evacuate!

00:03:06.269 --> 00:03:08.396 position:50% align:center
We can't let them get
caught up in all this!

00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:09.314 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Understood!

00:03:09.397 --> 00:03:10.440 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:03:10.523 --> 00:03:11.816 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Hans! Fritz!

00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:13.151 position:50% align:center
--[HANS PALDIN] Right!
--[FRITZ KRAUS] We're here!

00:03:13.234 --> 00:03:15.820 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA] Not so fast!
God wants as many

00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:19.115 position:50% align:center
sacrifices as possible, you see.

00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:22.660 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] I don't have
time to waste on you!

00:03:25.121 --> 00:03:28.625 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN] I've got an idea.
Why don't you fight me?

00:03:28.708 --> 00:03:30.126 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Thank you!

00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:32.587 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA]
Nuh-uh. I won't let--

00:03:32.671 --> 00:03:36.591 position:50% align:center
What did I just say?
You're fighting me now!

00:03:36.675 --> 00:03:40.804 position:50% align:center
We'll get there first--
we're faster than him!

00:03:40.887 --> 00:03:43.431 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA] Heh... Do you
realize who you're up against?

00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:45.100 position:50% align:center
Just because you're
angry doesn't mean

00:03:45.183 --> 00:03:47.477 position:50% align:center
you stand a chance
at besting me.

00:03:47.560 --> 00:03:51.314 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN] I'm not alone.
And he's angrier than me.

00:03:51.398 --> 00:03:54.609 position:50% align:center
This is all just one big game
to you, isn't it, jester?

00:03:54.693 --> 00:03:56.277 position:50% align:center
Maybe, so what?

00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:58.655 position:50% align:center
He risked his life to
set a friend straight.

00:03:58.738 --> 00:04:00.740 position:50% align:center
That takes an incredible
amount of heart.

00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:03.576 position:50% align:center
That you'd laugh at that tells
me all I need to know.

00:04:03.660 --> 00:04:06.413 position:50% align:center
You've completely lost your way!

00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:08.498 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:04:08.581 --> 00:04:11.876 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN yelling]

00:04:11.960 --> 00:04:14.462 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN]
Let's do this!

00:04:14.546 --> 00:04:16.131 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA] What happened
to the Rekkan custom

00:04:16.214 --> 00:04:18.466 position:50% align:center
of introducing yourself
before a fight?

00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:20.510 position:50% align:center
I thought that was
important to you.

00:04:20.593 --> 00:04:22.012 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN]
It is.

00:04:22.095 --> 00:04:27.726 position:50% align:center
But this isn't a fight--
it's an execution!

00:04:27.809 --> 00:04:29.477 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA]
How?

00:04:33.815 --> 00:04:37.819 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA]
I see, another irregular.

00:04:39.738 --> 00:04:41.197 position:50% align:center
[BOTH grunting]

00:04:41.281 --> 00:04:44.576 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN] Shu. Though we
went our separate ways,

00:04:44.659 --> 00:04:47.412 position:50% align:center
we once shared the same dream.

00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:49.831 position:50% align:center
I may not have agreed with him,

00:04:49.914 --> 00:04:51.458 position:50% align:center
but he believed in
what he was doing

00:04:51.541 --> 00:04:52.876 position:50% align:center
enough to risk his life.

00:04:52.959 --> 00:04:54.919 position:50% align:center
And you dare to mock the man?

00:04:55.003 --> 00:05:00.800 position:50% align:center
I won't allow you to get away
with that! Fury Cleave.

00:05:03.845 --> 00:05:06.222 position:50% align:center
How can this be?

00:05:11.227 --> 00:05:13.104 position:50% align:center
How pitiful, Shu.

00:05:13.188 --> 00:05:15.857 position:50% align:center
The man you betrayed
us for took your life.

00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:18.568 position:50% align:center
If only you hadn't entrusted
your dreams to him,

00:05:18.651 --> 00:05:22.489 position:50% align:center
you might be here with us now.

00:05:22.572 --> 00:05:25.950 position:50% align:center
But I will live on. And I'll
build a nation where the poor

00:05:26.034 --> 00:05:29.537 position:50% align:center
can live in peace--
the dream you cast aside.

00:05:29.621 --> 00:05:31.831 position:50% align:center
I hope you'll watch me
from above,

00:05:31.915 --> 00:05:34.876 position:50% align:center
with that smirk
you always had on.

00:05:44.094 --> 00:05:47.639 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
So, what now? What do we do?

00:05:47.722 --> 00:05:50.308 position:50% align:center
Might as well discuss it.
With Shu gone,

00:05:50.392 --> 00:05:52.602 position:50% align:center
I'm not sure we're left
with many options.

00:05:52.686 --> 00:05:54.854 position:50% align:center
We keep trying to return
Arrow to normal?

00:05:54.938 --> 00:05:56.898 position:50% align:center
As much as I would
love to do that,

00:05:56.981 --> 00:06:00.026 position:50% align:center
if Shu couldn't figure it out,
how are we going to?

00:06:00.110 --> 00:06:02.362 position:50% align:center
What good will come
from us giving up now?

00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:04.781 position:50% align:center
Easy for you to say,
you're royalty.

00:06:04.864 --> 00:06:07.242 position:50% align:center
We're nothing.
Just country folk.

00:06:07.325 --> 00:06:09.911 position:50% align:center
We only got this far
because of Shu and Arrow,

00:06:09.994 --> 00:06:11.496 position:50% align:center
but we're in over our heads.

00:06:11.579 --> 00:06:14.249 position:50% align:center
The world ending
is way beyond us!

00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:16.626 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but...
Even if you're right,

00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:18.211 position:50% align:center
there are things we can do!

00:06:18.294 --> 00:06:20.672 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:20.755 --> 00:06:24.092 position:50% align:center
Back in Edger Village, it felt
like any day could wind up

00:06:24.175 --> 00:06:28.722 position:50% align:center
being my last, life wasn't easy.
It never has been.

00:06:28.805 --> 00:06:32.559 position:50% align:center
Which is why I always
did what I could and--

00:06:32.642 --> 00:06:35.061 position:50% align:center
And is now really any different?

00:06:35.145 --> 00:06:37.522 position:50% align:center
Even without Arrow and Shu,

00:06:37.605 --> 00:06:41.026 position:50% align:center
we've still got the Granedger,
and Prax, and the others!

00:06:41.109 --> 00:06:44.696 position:50% align:center
We're way better off
than we were back then!

00:06:44.779 --> 00:06:48.241 position:50% align:center
And what's really scarier?
Some God or poverty?

00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:49.367 position:50% align:center
Oh, Bit.

00:06:49.451 --> 00:06:52.454 position:50% align:center
You're right.
We shouldn't give up.

00:06:53.705 --> 00:06:55.165 position:50% align:center
I have a request.

00:06:55.248 --> 00:06:57.834 position:50% align:center
Would you all be willing to
take Granedger to Lutoh?

00:06:57.917 --> 00:07:00.045 position:50% align:center
I'm just worried that the
citizens will be caught up

00:07:00.128 --> 00:07:01.921 position:50% align:center
in Rudolf and Rekka's battle.

00:07:02.005 --> 00:07:03.965 position:50% align:center
It's scary to think
what might happen.

00:07:04.049 --> 00:07:05.342 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL grunting]
But...

00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:07.052 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] You sure?
They chased you off.

00:07:07.135 --> 00:07:09.596 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTÉ] I know,
but Lutoh is my motherland.

00:07:09.679 --> 00:07:11.598 position:50% align:center
Even if there might
not be a tomorrow,

00:07:11.681 --> 00:07:13.558 position:50% align:center
I still want to help today.

00:07:13.641 --> 00:07:18.188 position:50% align:center
Understood. Then let's
save the Lutoh people!

00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:21.149 position:50% align:center
Now that you're yourself again,
lemme show you

00:07:21.232 --> 00:07:24.527 position:50% align:center
a little somethin'.
Shu gave me this!

00:07:24.611 --> 00:07:25.737 position:50% align:center
Seriously?

00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:27.280 position:50% align:center
Is that a new Warper?

00:07:27.364 --> 00:07:31.576 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Because we may be down,
but we're far from out!

00:07:32.577 --> 00:07:34.371 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
This will soon be a battlefield!

00:07:34.454 --> 00:07:36.998 position:50% align:center
Evacuate! Get as far
away as possible!

00:07:37.082 --> 00:07:38.333 position:50% align:center
[MAN A]
What's she doing here? Go home!

00:07:38.416 --> 00:07:40.126 position:50% align:center
[MAN E]
Oh, what is it this time?

00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:41.294 position:50% align:center
[MAN F]
Get lost, woudja?

00:07:41.378 --> 00:07:42.754 position:50% align:center
[MAN G]
Yeah! Go away!

00:07:42.837 --> 00:07:44.005 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN B]
You've done enough!

00:07:44.089 --> 00:07:45.799 position:50% align:center
[MAN K]
Why didn't you help us then?

00:07:45.882 --> 00:07:49.386 position:50% align:center
They're not gonna listen
to me, huh? Fine!

00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:51.888 position:50% align:center
[MAN L yelps]

00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:56.017 position:50% align:center
What the hell? Run!

00:07:56.101 --> 00:07:59.479 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] Yes, run!
Run or else you'll die!

00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:07.987 position:50% align:center
You must know this is pointless,
Armored Supreme.

00:08:08.071 --> 00:08:09.572 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Rudolph!

00:08:09.656 --> 00:08:12.909 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE] They'll all
disappear, because God wills it.

00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:15.286 position:50% align:center
For some reason they
continue to struggle

00:08:15.370 --> 00:08:17.706 position:50% align:center
but that's a welcome sight.

00:08:17.789 --> 00:08:18.832 position:50% align:center
"Welcome"?

00:08:18.915 --> 00:08:21.626 position:50% align:center
God wishes for the struggle.
It helps.

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:26.006 position:50% align:center
Humanity's pointless attempts to
survive is nourishment to God.

00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:27.799 position:50% align:center
So, what happens when
Lingalind is gone

00:08:27.882 --> 00:08:29.384 position:50% align:center
and you're all alone?

00:08:29.467 --> 00:08:31.928 position:50% align:center
Can you rule over a world
with no one in it?

00:08:32.012 --> 00:08:35.265 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
No. I'll be destroyed as well.

00:08:35.348 --> 00:08:39.102 position:50% align:center
The end of Lingalind will
also mean the end of me.

00:08:39.185 --> 00:08:41.062 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
What?

00:08:41.146 --> 00:08:45.191 position:50% align:center
God splits his soul and turns it
into the land we stand upon.

00:08:45.275 --> 00:08:49.237 position:50% align:center
The people grow that soul,
and eventually return it to God.

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:51.114 position:50% align:center
And if my soul
helps nourish God,

00:08:51.197 --> 00:08:54.909 position:50% align:center
I will gladly give it.
There is no greater joy.

00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:58.288 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] If that's how you
feel, what was Lutoh to you?

00:08:58.371 --> 00:09:01.249 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Lutoh? What meaning is there

00:09:01.332 --> 00:09:03.543 position:50% align:center
in something made by humans?

00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:07.172 position:50% align:center
Their hearts and behavior
are so fragile and erratic.

00:09:07.255 --> 00:09:10.383 position:50% align:center
I mean, think about it, all
it took was one little nudge

00:09:10.467 --> 00:09:13.470 position:50% align:center
of the heart and the people
of Lutoh's undying love

00:09:13.553 --> 00:09:16.848 position:50% align:center
for Princess Fine
turned to hatred.

00:09:16.931 --> 00:09:19.225 position:50% align:center
In truth, the tiniest
influence can turn

00:09:19.309 --> 00:09:22.937 position:50% align:center
a person's life upside down.
Make one kite look like a bird,

00:09:23.021 --> 00:09:24.939 position:50% align:center
and suddenly your
brother is in hell.

00:09:25.023 --> 00:09:28.485 position:50% align:center
What'd you-- What did you say?

00:09:29.903 --> 00:09:33.656 position:50% align:center
You're not telling me that
was your doing, are you?

00:09:33.740 --> 00:09:36.951 position:50% align:center
Fine's misery,
and Werner's grief...

00:09:37.035 --> 00:09:39.996 position:50% align:center
You mean all that suffering
was orchestrated by you?

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:41.956 position:50% align:center
Her misery was part
of the struggle,

00:09:42.040 --> 00:09:44.626 position:50% align:center
and therefore
an offering to God.

00:09:44.709 --> 00:09:47.295 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
You bastard!

00:09:48.338 --> 00:09:49.422 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Are you okay?

00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:50.715 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
You two stay out of this!

00:09:50.799 --> 00:09:52.258 position:50% align:center
But commander Prax!

00:09:52.342 --> 00:09:55.303 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] You demon. What
you've done is indefensible!

00:09:55.387 --> 00:09:57.597 position:50% align:center
You'll pay for it
with your head!

00:09:57.681 --> 00:10:00.266 position:50% align:center
God gave us this gift
of life for free.

00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:03.186 position:50% align:center
And without once
asking for our thanks.

00:10:03.269 --> 00:10:06.231 position:50% align:center
If that's not love,
then what is?

00:10:06.314 --> 00:10:11.569 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD groaning]

00:10:11.653 --> 00:10:13.321 position:50% align:center
The way you that
attack with such

00:10:13.405 --> 00:10:15.699 position:50% align:center
reckless hatred
reminds me of Werner.

00:10:15.782 --> 00:10:18.034 position:50% align:center
Perhaps I should
have expected that.

00:10:18.118 --> 00:10:18.993 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
My brother?

00:10:19.077 --> 00:10:20.328 position:50% align:center
Of course.

00:10:20.412 --> 00:10:22.831 position:50% align:center
When he learned the truth,
he did the same thing.

00:10:22.914 --> 00:10:25.250 position:50% align:center
He got in his Briheight
and charged right at me

00:10:25.333 --> 00:10:27.168 position:50% align:center
without the slightest plan.

00:10:27.252 --> 00:10:29.087 position:50% align:center
On the night of
the riots, I believe.

00:10:29.170 --> 00:10:33.425 position:50% align:center
Is that right? He was brave
in his final moments?

00:10:33.508 --> 00:10:36.803 position:50% align:center
I'm glad. You've given me more
reason to make him proud.

00:10:36.886 --> 00:10:39.347 position:50% align:center
Funny. Does betraying
one's country

00:10:39.431 --> 00:10:41.433 position:50% align:center
run in your family,
or are you two special?

00:10:41.516 --> 00:10:42.559 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Silence!

00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:44.602 position:50% align:center
I'll show you where
our loyalties lie,

00:10:44.686 --> 00:10:47.605 position:50% align:center
by finishing you off
with this attack!

00:10:50.358 --> 00:10:51.651 position:50% align:center
Would you look at that?

00:10:51.735 --> 00:10:54.446 position:50% align:center
Some bite. You're not all bark.

00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:57.532 position:50% align:center
[HANS PALDIN, FRITZ KRAUS]
Prax!

00:10:57.615 --> 00:10:59.492 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Are you upset, Supreme?

00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:02.162 position:50% align:center
Or perhaps frustrated?

00:11:02.245 --> 00:11:06.458 position:50% align:center
Be upset. Be frustrated.
Be angry and bitter.

00:11:06.541 --> 00:11:08.752 position:50% align:center
The fiercer the soul,
the more God's delight

00:11:08.835 --> 00:11:12.213 position:50% align:center
when it rejoins his own.
Oh, and don't you worry,

00:11:12.297 --> 00:11:14.591 position:50% align:center
your position on the
matter is irrelevant.

00:11:14.674 --> 00:11:18.428 position:50% align:center
God's love is for all to enjoy.

00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:23.141 position:50% align:center
Now, away to the realm
of God with you!

00:11:24.434 --> 00:11:26.895 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW yelling]

00:11:26.978 --> 00:11:27.979 position:50% align:center
Is that Arrow?

00:11:28.063 --> 00:11:30.106 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Prax, run!

00:11:33.401 --> 00:11:35.779 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:11:45.330 --> 00:11:49.292 position:50% align:center
Hey Rudolf! If you want to live,
bring everyone back now

00:11:49.376 --> 00:11:53.505 position:50% align:center
and while you're at it,
return me to normal!

00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:56.466 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Fine. Go on, do it.

00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:59.844 position:50% align:center
I'll gladly be erased by
the destroyer himself.

00:11:59.928 --> 00:12:00.804 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
What?

00:12:00.887 --> 00:12:01.930 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Do it!

00:12:02.013 --> 00:12:04.182 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
You asked for it! Huh...?

00:12:04.265 --> 00:12:07.143 position:50% align:center
What's wrong? Are you
not able to injure me?

00:12:07.227 --> 00:12:08.520 position:50% align:center
But why?

00:12:08.603 --> 00:12:10.605 position:50% align:center
Simple, because
it's meant to be.

00:12:10.689 --> 00:12:12.857 position:50% align:center
God must wish that I
remain in Lingalind

00:12:12.941 --> 00:12:15.235 position:50% align:center
to bear witness
to its eradication.

00:12:15.318 --> 00:12:17.320 position:50% align:center
And since you were sent by God,

00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:20.323 position:50% align:center
you're physically incapable
of opposing his wishes.

00:12:20.407 --> 00:12:21.324 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Dammit!

00:12:21.408 --> 00:12:28.415 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW groaning]

00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:30.583 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Rudolph! What did you do?

00:12:30.667 --> 00:12:33.586 position:50% align:center
Oh, are you guys still here?

00:12:33.670 --> 00:12:36.339 position:50% align:center
I'm afraid I'm going to have
to postpone our little tussle.

00:12:36.423 --> 00:12:37.507 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
What?

00:12:37.590 --> 00:12:39.342 position:50% align:center
It's just that the
main guest has arrived.

00:12:39.426 --> 00:12:40.719 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD grunts]

00:12:48.393 --> 00:12:51.771 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN] It seems normal
attacks won't work on you.

00:12:51.855 --> 00:12:56.776 position:50% align:center
All right, men!
Bring me 100 Bind Warpers!

00:12:56.860 --> 00:13:00.905 position:50% align:center
Keep in mind that Arrow's beam
destroys conviction particles.

00:13:00.989 --> 00:13:03.116 position:50% align:center
Beware of Muga as we engage

00:13:03.199 --> 00:13:06.036 position:50% align:center
and let us crush the
enemy of our world.

00:13:06.119 --> 00:13:09.539 position:50% align:center
Our opponent is Rudolph,
the pawn of God! Stay focused!

00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:10.540 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:13:10.623 --> 00:13:12.250 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Sir!

00:13:17.881 --> 00:13:21.968 position:50% align:center
[GOH ZANGA] Ha, ha. Kyo was
right! The skies evaded us for

00:13:22.052 --> 00:13:26.181 position:50% align:center
so long but the dreadnought's
Bind Warpers let us fly easily!

00:13:26.264 --> 00:13:27.557 position:50% align:center
[KYO MEIKETSU chuckles]

00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:29.559 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN] Are you sure you wish
to combine with me?

00:13:29.642 --> 00:13:31.811 position:50% align:center
Even when you can
fly on your own?

00:13:31.895 --> 00:13:35.315 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN] You are my wings.
I decided that long ago.

00:13:35.398 --> 00:13:36.858 position:50% align:center
Sir!

00:13:39.861 --> 00:13:42.864 position:50% align:center
Here we are Rudolf!
Just as I had promised!

00:13:42.947 --> 00:13:45.158 position:50% align:center
The Republic of Rekka
has returned to slaughter

00:13:45.241 --> 00:13:46.993 position:50% align:center
you and your so called deity!

00:13:47.077 --> 00:13:50.830 position:50% align:center
Ahh, it's time to greet
our guests, Arrow.

00:13:50.914 --> 00:13:52.916 position:50% align:center
Can't control my body!

00:13:52.999 --> 00:13:55.126 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
Diving Formation!

00:13:56.920 --> 00:13:59.881 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Zetsu, run!

00:13:59.964 --> 00:14:02.300 position:50% align:center
I'll erase you, too!

00:14:02.384 --> 00:14:04.052 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
I wonder about that!

00:14:04.135 --> 00:14:05.512 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW gasps]

00:14:06.721 --> 00:14:08.765 position:50% align:center
What happened? Did he
slice through the beam?

00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:10.016 position:50% align:center
I don't think so.

00:14:10.100 --> 00:14:12.227 position:50% align:center
It's like he twisted it
before impact, somehow!

00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:15.355 position:50% align:center
Well spotted, Kai! That's
precisely what I've done!

00:14:15.438 --> 00:14:17.899 position:50% align:center
I repelled the killer beam
using a high concentration

00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:20.902 position:50% align:center
of conviction particles
from the surrounding air!

00:14:20.985 --> 00:14:22.904 position:50% align:center
That's not good enough--
you're just defending!

00:14:22.987 --> 00:14:24.489 position:50% align:center
You can't beat me!

00:14:24.572 --> 00:14:26.741 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
I wonder about that, too!

00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:28.243 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW groans]

00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:31.287 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN] Now's our chance!
Everyone, attack Rudolph!

00:14:31.371 --> 00:14:32.831 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Right!

00:14:36.418 --> 00:14:37.836 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE chuckles]

00:14:37.919 --> 00:14:39.796 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW screams]

00:14:39.879 --> 00:14:44.759 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN laughing]

00:14:47.762 --> 00:14:50.974 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
Dragon Reflection Roar!

00:14:51.057 --> 00:14:52.392 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:53.476 --> 00:14:58.273 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
That's Zetsu for you. However...

00:14:58.356 --> 00:15:00.817 position:50% align:center
And a little this...

00:15:07.073 --> 00:15:10.493 position:50% align:center
Get back, warriors, quickly!

00:15:10.577 --> 00:15:11.828 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
I'll help!

00:15:11.911 --> 00:15:13.329 position:50% align:center
Fine, suit yourself!

00:15:13.413 --> 00:15:15.498 position:50% align:center
I think I will.

00:15:15.582 --> 00:15:16.750 position:50% align:center
[MAN N]
What is that?

00:15:16.833 --> 00:15:19.753 position:50% align:center
[MAN O]
Is It a monster?

00:15:19.836 --> 00:15:21.212 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW grunts]

00:15:21.296 --> 00:15:23.423 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN] If you continue
to protect Rudolf,

00:15:23.506 --> 00:15:25.342 position:50% align:center
I'll strike you down myself.

00:15:25.425 --> 00:15:28.219 position:50% align:center
That's exactly what I want.
Just erase me already.

00:15:28.303 --> 00:15:30.055 position:50% align:center
You might be the only
person in the world

00:15:30.138 --> 00:15:31.306 position:50% align:center
who's got a chance.

00:15:31.389 --> 00:15:33.641 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
That's really what you want?

00:15:33.725 --> 00:15:37.228 position:50% align:center
Now that we've lost Shu,
no one can save me

00:15:37.312 --> 00:15:39.898 position:50% align:center
and if all I'll do
is make people suffer,

00:15:39.981 --> 00:15:42.692 position:50% align:center
then I'd much rather be killed
than inflict any more pain.

00:15:42.776 --> 00:15:44.277 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
What did you say?

00:15:44.361 --> 00:15:48.823 position:50% align:center
You speak as if I'm inferior
to Shu. That upsets me.

00:15:48.907 --> 00:15:51.743 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
But what can you even do?

00:15:51.826 --> 00:15:55.246 position:50% align:center
Don't you dare underestimate
Zetsu Daidan.

00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:56.873 position:50% align:center
If you're resigned to death,

00:15:56.956 --> 00:15:59.250 position:50% align:center
at least outwit God
while you're alive!

00:15:59.334 --> 00:16:02.462 position:50% align:center
And if you can't control
yourself, I'll do it for you.

00:16:02.545 --> 00:16:05.757 position:50% align:center
You can't... Zetsu!

00:16:05.840 --> 00:16:07.592 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Majesty!

00:16:17.227 --> 00:16:20.772 position:50% align:center
Now, Arrow!
Together we will triumph!

00:16:20.855 --> 00:16:22.732 position:50% align:center
Let us crush Rudolf!

00:16:22.816 --> 00:16:26.277 position:50% align:center
You're young! What happened?

00:16:26.361 --> 00:16:27.946 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
Not bad, eh?

00:16:28.029 --> 00:16:31.032 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Guess not. Let's do this, Zetsu!

00:16:31.116 --> 00:16:32.659 position:50% align:center
"Emperor" Zetsu.

00:16:32.742 --> 00:16:37.247 position:50% align:center
Yeah, yeah, my bad.
Let's go, Emperor Zetsu!

00:16:37.330 --> 00:16:39.791 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN] Rudolf!
I seem to recall you saying

00:16:39.874 --> 00:16:44.754 position:50% align:center
God sent Arrow to Lingalind
because he feared me, correct?

00:16:44.838 --> 00:16:46.089 position:50% align:center
Then I think it's only fitting

00:16:46.172 --> 00:16:48.591 position:50% align:center
that I use God's own
weapon against him.

00:16:48.675 --> 00:16:53.763 position:50% align:center
First, I'll take your head,
and then I'll take his.

00:16:53.847 --> 00:16:56.766 position:50% align:center
Now... let the slaughter begin!

00:16:56.850 --> 00:16:59.394 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN laughing]

00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:03.106 position:50% align:center
He's rebuilding his body faster
than Arrow's able to destroy it!

00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:04.649 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
Ha!

00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:06.484 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Majesty!

00:17:07.819 --> 00:17:09.487 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Majesty!

00:17:11.239 --> 00:17:14.325 position:50% align:center
Just look at you. I said
that arrogance of yours

00:17:14.409 --> 00:17:17.954 position:50% align:center
would destroy the world,
did I not?

00:17:18.038 --> 00:17:20.582 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
Won't you fight, pawn of God?

00:17:20.665 --> 00:17:23.877 position:50% align:center
If that is what you wish of me.

00:17:26.087 --> 00:17:28.465 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:17:31.176 --> 00:17:35.096 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Behold, my Briheight, Diostrage.

00:17:35.180 --> 00:17:39.893 position:50% align:center
My conviction is thus:
"God is everything."

00:17:39.976 --> 00:17:42.103 position:50% align:center
Eradicating you should
have been Arrow's role,

00:17:42.187 --> 00:17:45.357 position:50% align:center
but oh well.
Can't have everything.

00:17:45.440 --> 00:17:47.525 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN]
What is that huge monstrosity?

00:17:47.609 --> 00:17:49.235 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
"Diobenedica."

00:17:49.319 --> 00:17:51.071 position:50% align:center
To put it in terms
you'll understand,

00:17:51.154 --> 00:17:55.658 position:50% align:center
it's something like a
dreadnought for me.

00:17:55.742 --> 00:18:00.330 position:50% align:center
Now, you shall obey
the will of God!

00:18:04.918 --> 00:18:06.461 position:50% align:center
What? Just like that?

00:18:06.544 --> 00:18:08.213 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Given the obvious power gap,

00:18:08.296 --> 00:18:10.507 position:50% align:center
I was hoping to avoid
showing off like this.

00:18:10.590 --> 00:18:12.884 position:50% align:center
But what can you do?

00:18:12.967 --> 00:18:15.261 position:50% align:center
--[SOLDIER A] What is this?
--[SOLDIER B] Look out!

00:18:15.345 --> 00:18:16.971 position:50% align:center
[REKKA SOLDIER D]
Help us!

00:18:17.055 --> 00:18:19.140 position:50% align:center
Warriors, return to
Dairekka, right now!

00:18:19.224 --> 00:18:21.518 position:50% align:center
You won't last out there!

00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:27.148 position:50% align:center
Really? We don't
stand a chance, do we?

00:18:27.232 --> 00:18:30.735 position:50% align:center
[GROUP groaning]

00:18:30.819 --> 00:18:31.820 position:50% align:center
[FRITZ KRAUS]
Hans!

00:18:31.903 --> 00:18:33.613 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Fritz! Hans!

00:18:33.697 --> 00:18:38.952 position:50% align:center
Begone! Especially you, Zetsu,
heretic of the world!

00:18:39.035 --> 00:18:41.830 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN grunting]

00:18:41.913 --> 00:18:43.540 position:50% align:center
Hang in there, man!

00:18:43.623 --> 00:18:44.874 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN grunts]

00:18:44.958 --> 00:18:47.085 position:50% align:center
This is the end of
the line for you.

00:18:47.168 --> 00:18:49.212 position:50% align:center
God's love cannot be defeated!

00:18:49.295 --> 00:18:53.967 position:50% align:center
Granarrow Lovsolute Vertical,
fire maximum output!

00:18:59.431 --> 00:19:01.182 position:50% align:center
[HANS PALDIN]
Wait, is this...?

00:19:01.266 --> 00:19:02.809 position:50% align:center
Lady Fine!

00:19:02.892 --> 00:19:04.811 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Well? Did we make it in time?

00:19:04.894 --> 00:19:08.231 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] That's a new top
speed record. And I'm beat!

00:19:08.314 --> 00:19:09.357 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL]
Good job, Elsha!

00:19:09.441 --> 00:19:10.400 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Heh...

00:19:10.483 --> 00:19:12.027 position:50% align:center
Please everyone, don't let up!

00:19:12.110 --> 00:19:13.737 position:50% align:center
The fight is still
far from over!

00:19:13.820 --> 00:19:16.698 position:50% align:center
I hoped you would understand,
Princess of False Love.

00:19:16.781 --> 00:19:19.451 position:50% align:center
Why do you hinder
God's gracious blessing?

00:19:19.534 --> 00:19:22.203 position:50% align:center
Why wouldn't I want to stop
the destruction of the world?

00:19:22.287 --> 00:19:24.622 position:50% align:center
Call it whatever you want,
we're not accepting it!

00:19:24.706 --> 00:19:26.374 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
You're all hopeless.

00:19:26.458 --> 00:19:28.376 position:50% align:center
You defy God's will
and cling to your

00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:31.212 position:50% align:center
insignificant lives like
they actually matter.

00:19:31.296 --> 00:19:33.590 position:50% align:center
Why can't you see that
it's that very hubris

00:19:33.673 --> 00:19:36.634 position:50% align:center
that caused this
in the first place?

00:19:36.718 --> 00:19:40.472 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN] Fine. Thanks
for your aid but stand back.

00:19:40.555 --> 00:19:43.266 position:50% align:center
Your love won't work this time,
not against him.

00:19:43.350 --> 00:19:46.811 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTÉ]
Is that Emperor Zetsu?

00:19:46.895 --> 00:19:47.854 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN]
That's right!

00:19:47.937 --> 00:19:48.897 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Huh?

00:19:48.980 --> 00:19:50.523 position:50% align:center
Wait Arrow, you let
Zetsu wield you?

00:19:50.607 --> 00:19:52.609 position:50% align:center
I figure if I've got
this destructive power,

00:19:52.692 --> 00:19:55.820 position:50% align:center
the two of us might as
well use it against Rudolf!

00:19:55.904 --> 00:19:58.531 position:50% align:center
Leave it to us!
Zetsu and I will win!

00:19:58.615 --> 00:19:59.574 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Oh, please.

00:19:59.657 --> 00:20:00.992 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW grunts]

00:20:01.076 --> 00:20:02.285 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE] Understand
that with your deaths,

00:20:02.369 --> 00:20:04.788 position:50% align:center
the world shall regain harmony.

00:20:04.871 --> 00:20:06.498 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN grunts]

00:20:06.581 --> 00:20:07.916 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Just do it.

00:20:07.999 --> 00:20:12.253 position:50% align:center
Sacrifice your lives
for the future!

00:20:12.337 --> 00:20:16.758 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Hold on! Losing control here!

00:20:16.841 --> 00:20:19.594 position:50% align:center
[ZETSU DAIDAN grunting]

00:20:19.678 --> 00:20:24.641 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE chuckles]

00:20:24.724 --> 00:20:26.643 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
God's blessing has no limits.

00:20:26.726 --> 00:20:30.605 position:50% align:center
It shall spread far and wide!
None can escape it!

00:20:30.689 --> 00:20:34.901 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
You wanna bet?

00:20:34.984 --> 00:20:38.405 position:50% align:center
Bit Namital has arrived!
Betcha didn't expect me!

00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:40.156 position:50% align:center
--Whoa, Bit!
--What are you doing here?

00:20:40.240 --> 00:20:42.367 position:50% align:center
Get away from there--
you don't stand a chance!

00:20:42.450 --> 00:20:44.119 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE] You can't
bluff your way out of this one.

00:20:44.202 --> 00:20:45.704 position:50% align:center
It's over.

00:20:45.787 --> 00:20:47.956 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Oh, shit. I'm gonna mess myself!

00:20:48.039 --> 00:20:51.084 position:50% align:center
Doesn't matter!
I've gotta do this!

00:20:51.167 --> 00:20:53.712 position:50% align:center
Then I guess it's a good
thing I'm not bluffin'.

00:20:53.795 --> 00:20:56.464 position:50% align:center
A Bind Warper? Don't do
this Bit, you'll die!

00:20:56.548 --> 00:20:57.674 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Nuh-uh, look!

00:20:57.757 --> 00:21:00.218 position:50% align:center
This bad boy was made
by Demyne of Lutoh,

00:21:00.301 --> 00:21:02.137 position:50% align:center
then perfected by Shu from Rekka

00:21:02.220 --> 00:21:04.389 position:50% align:center
using Granedger
United's technology!

00:21:04.472 --> 00:21:06.224 position:50% align:center
A three-country Bind Warper!

00:21:06.307 --> 00:21:09.394 position:50% align:center
The pinnacle of
Lingalind's evolution!

00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:10.895 position:50% align:center
Shu helped?

00:21:10.979 --> 00:21:13.940 position:50% align:center
And who better to carry on
their legacy than yours truly?

00:21:14.024 --> 00:21:17.861 position:50% align:center
Edger's Admiral of Tactics and
humanity's secret weapon!

00:21:17.944 --> 00:21:21.781 position:50% align:center
Me! Bit Namital, the Great!

00:21:21.865 --> 00:21:23.867 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:21:26.453 --> 00:21:27.829 position:50% align:center
Is that even a Briheight?

00:21:27.912 --> 00:21:30.749 position:50% align:center
I don't know. It just looks
like a giant Bind Warper.

00:21:30.832 --> 00:21:33.668 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL] This is the power
Shu entrusted to me.

00:21:33.752 --> 00:21:36.504 position:50% align:center
Briheight: "Kaiten"!

00:21:36.588 --> 00:21:37.797 position:50% align:center
All right, I'll bite.

00:21:37.881 --> 00:21:39.841 position:50% align:center
How do you expect to
fight me with that thing?

00:21:39.924 --> 00:21:43.053 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Like this! Elsha, let's do it!

00:21:43.136 --> 00:21:44.262 position:50% align:center
Do what?

00:21:44.346 --> 00:21:46.181 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL] What else?
We're gonna combine!

00:21:46.264 --> 00:21:48.016 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER VOICE]
Manifest Armor.

00:21:48.099 --> 00:21:53.772 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL] This is it
the Briheight Granedger!

00:21:57.025 --> 00:21:59.736 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Don't underestimate humans!

00:21:59.819 --> 00:22:02.238 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
How absurd.

00:22:03.990 --> 00:22:06.910 position:50% align:center
Are you kidding me? That was
just a punch, wasn't it?

00:22:06.993 --> 00:22:08.578 position:50% align:center
How the hell did they
break my jail

00:22:08.661 --> 00:22:11.164 position:50% align:center
